---
export const prerender = true;
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<Layout
  title="Methodology — How Our Rankings, News & Data Are Produced"
  description="Transparent explanation of how ScrabbleWordsFinder produces world rankings, curates news, calculates statistics, and maintains data quality. Our editorial standards."
  keywords="scrabble rankings methodology, how rankings work, scrabble news curation, data methodology, editorial policy, scrabble statistics methodology"
>

<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">

  <h1 class="text-3xl font-light text-white mb-3">Methodology</h1>
  <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-10">How we produce our rankings, curate news, calculate statistics, and maintain data quality.</p>

  <!-- Rankings -->
  <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">World Rankings</h2>

  <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">📐 How Rankings Are Calculated</p>
    <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Our rankings are based on <span class="text-white font-medium">publicly available WESPA tournament results</span>. We track official WESPA-rated events and reflect the most recent data available from wespa.org.</p>
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">We maintain three ranking types:</p>

  <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
    <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">WESPA Ratings:</span> Elo-style ratings based on over-the-board (OTB) tournament performance. Higher-rated opponents yield more rating points. Updated after major tournaments.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">YTD Rankings:</span> Cumulative Year-to-Date points from October 1 to September 30. Players' best 5 tournament results count. Used for Summit Cup qualification (top 24).</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Online Ratings:</span> Separate from OTB. Based on WESPA-sanctioned online tournament events. Different player pool and rating scale.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-gray-300">Update frequency:</strong> Rankings are updated manually after major tournaments, typically within 1-2 weeks of results being published by WESPA. We aim to reflect the most current publicly available data.</p>

  <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mt-3"><strong class="text-gray-300">Limitations:</strong> Our rankings are approximate reflections of official WESPA data. For authoritative, real-time ratings, refer to <a href="https://wespa.org/ratings/online-ratings" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">wespa.org</a>.</p>

  <!-- News -->
  <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-emerald-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-emerald-400 pl-4">Latest News Curation</h2>

  <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-emerald-500/30 bg-emerald-950/20">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-emerald-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">📰 How News Is Sourced</p>
    <p class="text-base text-gray-200">News is fetched via <span class="text-white font-medium">Tavily web search API</span> with Scrabble-specific queries, then optionally summarised by AI, and requires <span class="text-white font-medium">manual admin approval</span> before publication.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 News Pipeline</p>
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">1</span>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong>Search:</strong> Tavily API queries rotate daily across 7 Scrabble-related keywords. Results filtered to last 7-30 days.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">2</span>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong>Filter:</strong> Generic topic/tag pages rejected. Only article-level URLs with real content are kept.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">3</span>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong>Summarise:</strong> AI optionally improves snippet summaries (titles and URLs always come directly from search results).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">4</span>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong>Deduplicate:</strong> Items matching titles from the last 7 days are skipped.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">5</span>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong>Approve:</strong> Admin reviews each item and approves, hides, or deletes. Only approved items appear publicly.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 leading-relaxed"><strong class="text-gray-300">Source attribution:</strong> Every news item links to its original source. We do not claim original reporting — we aggregate and summarise with attribution.</p>

  <!-- Statistics -->
  <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Statistics & Data</h2>

  <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/20">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">📊 Data Sources</p>
    <p class="text-base text-gray-200">All Scrabble statistics are derived from the <span class="text-white font-medium">official SOWPODS (Collins Scrabble Words)</span> dictionary and standard Scrabble tile distribution. No proprietary or copyrighted word lists are redistributed.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
    <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-amber-400 font-semibold">Tile values & distribution:</span> Based on the standard English Scrabble set (100 tiles). These are factual, publicly known values published by Hasbro/Mattel.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-amber-400 font-semibold">Word counts & scores:</span> Computed programmatically from the SOWPODS dictionary. Scores calculated using standard letter values.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-amber-400 font-semibold">Probability calculations:</span> Based on combinatorics from the standard 100-tile bag distribution.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Editorial -->
  <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-gray-300 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-gray-500 pl-4">Editorial Standards</h2>

  <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
    <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
      <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ We Do</p>
      <ul class="text-xs text-gray-400 space-y-1 mt-2">
        <li>• Cite sources for all claims</li>
        <li>• Link to original WESPA/NASPA data</li>
        <li>• Attribute news to original publishers</li>
        <li>• Correct errors when identified</li>
        <li>• Update rankings after major events</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
      <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ We Don't</p>
      <ul class="text-xs text-gray-400 space-y-1 mt-2">
        <li>• Fabricate statistics or rankings</li>
        <li>• Publish unverified news without review</li>
        <li>• Redistribute copyrighted word lists</li>
        <li>• Present AI-generated content as fact</li>
        <li>• Claim official WESPA/NASPA affiliation</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Corrections -->
  <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-gray-300 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-gray-500 pl-4">Corrections Policy</h2>

  <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">If you identify an error in our rankings, statistics, or content, please <a href="/contact/" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">contact us</a>. We will investigate and correct verified errors promptly. Corrections are noted in our <a href="/releases/" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">release notes</a>.</p>

  <!-- Feeds -->
  <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-cyan-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 pl-4">RSS Feeds</h2>

  <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">Subscribe to our content via RSS:</p>

  <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-2">
    <a href="/rss/news.xml" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-cyan-700 transition-all">
      <span class="text-cyan-400">📰</span>
      <span class="text-sm text-gray-300">/rss/news.xml — Latest Scrabble News</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/rss/rankings.xml" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-cyan-700 transition-all">
      <span class="text-cyan-400">🏆</span>
      <span class="text-sm text-gray-300">/rss/rankings.xml — World Rankings (Top 25)</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/rss/tournaments.xml" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-cyan-700 transition-all">
      <span class="text-cyan-400">📅</span>
      <span class="text-sm text-gray-300">/rss/tournaments.xml — Tournament Calendar</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/rss/wotd.xml" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-cyan-700 transition-all">
      <span class="text-cyan-400">📖</span>
      <span class="text-sm text-gray-300">/rss/wotd.xml — Word of the Day (last 14 days)</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/rss/challenge.xml" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-cyan-700 transition-all">
      <span class="text-cyan-400">🎯</span>
      <span class="text-sm text-gray-300">/rss/challenge.xml — Daily Challenges (rack + anagram)</span>
    </a>
  </div>

</div>

</Layout>
